<h2>Usage guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Always use the GOV.UK colour palette as specified</li>
    <li>Ensure all text meets WCAG 2.2 contrast requirements (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)</li>
    <li>Use functional colours for their intended purpose (error for errors, success for success messages, etc.)</li>
    <li>Test colour combinations for accessibility before using in production</li>
    <li>Never rely on colour alone to convey information</li>
</ul>

<p>
    For the complete GOV.UK colour palette including Teal, Magenta, Orange, and Brown variants, 
    refer to the <a href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/styles/colour/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GOV.UK Design System colour documentation</a>.
</p>
